      <section eId="sec_12_3_208">
        <num>12-3-208</num>
        <content>
          <p>Resolutions for the issuance of bonds may be adopted without any other proceedings or the happening of any other conditions or things than those proceedings, conditions, and things which are specified or required by this part. Any resolution providing for the issuance of bonds under this part shall become effective immediately upon its passage and need not be published or posted. Any such resolution may be passed at any regular, special, or adjourned meeting of the association by a majority of its members.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1958, p. 61, ยง 18.)</p>
